"Two laughing gulls (Leucophaeus atricilla) share a moment at low tide, each embodying a different rhythm of coastal life. One gull stands poised in the shallow water, balanced on a single leg like a sentinel, its reflection shimmering faintly beneath it. The other gull is airborne, wings outstretched in full span, caught mid-flight with sunlight illuminating the feathers—each plume etched in light and motion.

The water is calm, rippling gently across the sand, which is textured with ridges and shallow pools. The gulls are framed by this serene landscape, where stillness and movement coexist. The standing gull seems contemplative, while the flying one arcs with energy, casting a fleeting shadow below.
